The paper proposes a deep learning model for predicting air pollution in a city using spatiotemporal datasets. The model uses Convolutional Long Short-Term Memory (ConvLSTM) which is a combination of Convolutional Neural Networks and Long Short-Term Memory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
